# FocusBot TypeScript / React Rules

Reference: `docs/coding-guidelines.md` (TypeScript / React section). Follow when editing `.ts` or `.tsx` files.

## Style

- **Strict TypeScript** (`strict: true`). No `any` unless truly unavoidable.
- **ESM modules** (`"type": "module"`). Use `import` / `export`.
- **Functional components** only — no class components.
- **Named exports** preferred over default exports.

## Naming

| Kind | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Components | PascalCase | `SessionCard`, `FocusGauge` |
| Hooks | `use` prefix | `useAuth`, `usePaddle` |
| Files (components) | PascalCase `.tsx` | `BillingPage.tsx` |
| Files (utilities) | camelCase `.ts` | `apiClient.ts` |
| Interfaces/Types | PascalCase, no `I` prefix | `SessionResponse`, `AppState` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `APP_KEYS`, `API_BASE_URL` |

## React Patterns

- `useState` + `useEffect` for local state; React Context for cross-component state.
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks. Always clean up subscriptions/timers in effect return.
- Use `useCallback` / `useMemo` only when there is a measurable benefit.
- Event handlers: `handleClick`, `onSubmit` naming.

## Error Handling

- API calls return structured results (`{ ok, data }` | `{ ok: false, status, error }`). No thrown exceptions for expected failures.
- Use `try`/`catch` only around truly exceptional operations (network, JSON parse).
- Always handle loading and error states in UI components.

## Imports

- Group: React → third-party → project absolute → relative. Blank line between groups.
- Prefer path aliases where configured.

## CSS

- Plain CSS files with `--fb-*` CSS variables for colors, spacing, elevation.
- 3 surface layers: page (darkest `#110E1A`) < section (`#1C1730`) < card (`#2A2242`).
- Scope styles under page/component wrappers. No global element selectors.
- Always provide visible `:focus-visible` indicators.

## Pre-commit Checklist

- [ ] No `any` types
- [ ] Named exports used
- [ ] Effects have cleanup functions where needed
- [ ] API calls use structured error returns
- [ ] Accessible: focus states, alt text, ARIA labels
- [ ] No hardcoded colors — use CSS variables
